  <h1>🧤 Yashin Trophy</h1>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>⚽ What is the Yashin Trophy?</h2>
    <p>
      The <strong>Yashin Trophy</strong> is an annual football award presented to the <strong>best performing goalkeeper</strong> in the world. 
      Named after legendary Soviet goalkeeper <strong>Lev Yashin</strong> — the only goalkeeper to ever win the Ballon d'Or — 
      this award honors elite performances <em>between the posts</em> on the global stage 🌍.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>📌 Key Facts</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>📅 <strong>Inception:</strong> 2019</li>
      <li>🏆 <strong>Presented By:</strong> <em>France Football</em> magazine</li>
      <li>🎖️ <strong>Named After:</strong> Lev Yashin (Ballon d’Or winner in 1963)</li>
      <li>🌐 <strong>Eligibility:</strong> Goalkeepers from all over the world</li>
      <li>🧠 <strong>Criteria:</strong> Performance, clean sheets, consistency, and big-game impact</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>🥇 Notable Winners</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>🇧🇷 <strong>Alisson Becker</strong> – First winner in 2019 (Liverpool)</li>
      <li>🇮🇹 <strong>Gianluigi Donnarumma</strong> – 2021 winner after Euro 2020 heroics</li>
      <li>🇧🇪 <strong>Thibaut Courtois</strong> – 2022 winner for Champions League dominance</li>
      <li>🇦🇷 <strong>Emiliano Martínez</strong> – 2023 winner after World Cup performance</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section fun-fact">
    ✨ <strong>Fun Fact:</strong> The Yashin Trophy is voted on by the same panel of journalists who choose the Ballon d'Or — keeping it prestigious and competitive! 🧤🌍
  </div>

